The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, July 23: A mentally unstable passenger on an Indigo flight from Delhi was arrested after he claimed there was a bomb on board and that the aircraft should be diverted to Pakistan.          Sanjay Malik, 28, from Haryana, created panic by saying there was a bomb in the juice packet he had been served. He was handed over to the CISF after the plane landed in Mumbai. Sustained interrogation revealed he was mentally unstable, CISF commandant Shiv Kumar said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The railways will introduce charging facilities for cellphones in sleeper class coaches of every train, minister of state for railways K.H. Muniyappa told the Lok Sabha on Thursday.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A cleaner killed a fellow employee who had tried to stop him from stealing cash from their office in south Mumbai on Wednesday. Pradeep Singh struck Suresh Valmiki on the head with a steel rod during the scuffle. Singh was arrested while trying to escape by climbing down a drainage pipe.                  
	 Coimbatore (PTI): A central jail warden has been arrested on charges of supplying ganja to the prisoners. He allegedly used to smuggle ganja into the jail by stuffing it in his shoes and distributing the stuff through two prisoners.
                                                                                                                           
